Sentencas: Films made of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 (LSM) were deposited by pulsed direct current (DQ magnetron sputtering at ambient temperature.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: After annealing in air at temperature from 600 to 900 degrees C, the crystallographic structure and phase composition were studied using X-ray diffraction and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: Area specific resistance (ASR) of the coated specimen was measured with the standard DC four-point approach at 750 degrees C in air.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: Adding oxygen during deposition increased crystallization temperature from an amorphous to a perovskite phase and decreased the deposition rate.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: After annealing, excess oxygen in the films produced additional oxide segregations at the specimen surface and left bubble holes after spallation.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: The specimen ASR after 1050 h at 760 degrees C was 39.5 m Omega.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: The degradation rate was 3.5 mfl per 1000 h, considerably lower than the standard for auxiliary power unit application.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering

Sentencas: Preliminary results in this study show that LSM films deposited by pulsed DC magnetron sputtering are good candidates for protective coating of solid oxide fuel cell interconnects.
Titulo: Structural characterization of La0.67Sr0.33MnO3 protective coatings for solid oxide fuel cell interconnect deposited by pulsed magnetron sputtering
